            code: `Given:
  • Camera intrinsics K (from calibration)
  • Camera pose [R | t] (from SLAM/tracking)
  • Virtual 3D point X_virt

Projection:
  x_screen = K · [R | t] · X_virt

For correct occlusion:
  • Render real-world depth map
  • Compare virtual point depth Z_virt
    with real depth Z_real at same pixel
  • If Z_virt > Z_real: occluded (hide)
  • If Z_virt < Z_real: visible (render)

Lighting:
  • Estimate real light sources from image
  • Apply to virtual material (PBR shading)
  • Match shadows onto detected planes`,
