            code: `Hidden Chain 1 (Exertion):
  States: Resting, Walking, Running
  Transition: P(S₁ₜ | S₁ₜ₋₁)

Hidden Chain 2 (Emotion):
  States: Calm, Anxious, Stressed
  Transition: P(S₂ₜ | S₂ₜ₋₁)

Observation (Heart Rate):
  Oₜ = f(S₁ₜ, S₂ₜ) + noise

Example inference:
  Observed: 120 bpm (baseline 70)
  Walking (20) + Stressed (30) = 120 ✓
  Resting (0) + Stressed (30) = 100 ✗
  Running (40) + Calm (0) = 110 ✗

Result: most likely state = Walking + Stressed.`,
            output: 'FHMM separates independent hidden processes and infers their joint state from observations.',
