            title: 'Logistic Regression Model',
            code: `Log-odds (logit):
  z = β₀ + β₁x₁ + β₂x₂ + ... + βₖxₖ

Probability:
  P(Y=1|X) = σ(z) = 1 / (1 + e⁻ᶻ)

Decision boundary (default):
  If P(Y=1|X) ≥ 0.5 → Predict Class 1
  If P(Y=1|X) < 0.5 → Predict Class 0

Odds interpretation:
  Odds = P / (1 - P) = eᶻ
  log(Odds) = z = β₀ + β₁x₁ + ...

A one-unit increase in xᵢ multiplies
odds by e^(βᵢ).`,
